1.Rename the continer
  command : docker rename continer-name re-name

  example : dokcer rename inspiring alma

  here, inspring is a already given name and 'alma' is rename

2.Give the continer name directly if you create a continer
  command & example : docker run -itd --name jenkins almalinux /bin/bash

3.Give the port number to the continer

  command & example : docker run -itd --name jenkins -p 8080:8080 almalinux /bin/bash

4.Give the privileges to the continer
  command & example :
     docker run -itd --name jenkins --privileged=true -p 8080:8080 -p 5000:5000 /sbin/init

 here, -p 5000:5000 is a redirect port number
 
5.Enter into the exit continer
  
 command : docker attach continer-id 
           docker attach continer-name

 command : docker exec -it continer-id /bin/bash

 example : docker exec -it 8a0519b81238 /bin/bash

6.Applying the commands outside of the continer
 
 command : docker exec -it continer-id  command /bin/bash

 example : docker exec -it 8a0519b81238 yum update -y /bin/bash

 >check the continer size :docker ps -s

